Rating: 4
I doubled the cayenne and the lemon juice. I left on the tails and sauted the shrimp in peanut oil till crisp. They can be frozen: after cooling on a rack, put in a freezer bag and remove the air. Surprisingly, the aioli also froze well: placed in a freezer bag and flattened - again with the air removed. I re-heated the shrimp at 300F without defrosting; the aioli was defrosted by the time the shrimp was done.

