Rating: 4
Absolutely fantastic. I butterflied the shrimp and coated them in the cornmeal, then cooked them at the last moment when our guests arrived. I pan fried the shrimp--I don't think you have to deep fry them. I used cayenne to taste, and remember if you make the aioli ahead that it will get spicier as it sits. I coated chicken cubes with cornmeal the next night to use the extra aioli, and that was also super. A keeper!

